<text>Idiazabal is a town and municipality in the Goierri region of the province of Gipuzkoa, in the autonomous community of the Basque Country, northern Spain.

The area has given its name to the renowned Idiazabal cheese of the region, one of the best-known products of the Basque cuisine.

